Busting Common sleep myths with @wakefitco in #ghibli style 
These are some of the questions that i get asked most, so here's a fun informative reel for you all!

QndA- 
	1.Is 8 hours of sleep the magic number for everyone, or does it vary?
➡️ It varies! Most adults need 7-9 hours, but factors like age, lifestyle, and genetics play a role.
2.Can listening to music or white noise improve sleep quality?
➡️ Yes! Calm music, white noise, and nature sounds can help people fall asleep faster and stay asleep longer by masking background noise.
3.Can drinking coffee in the afternoon ruin your sleep, even hours later?
➡️ Yes! Caffeine can stay in your system for up to 6-8 hours, making it harder to fall asleep and reducing deep sleep quality.
4. Do sleep interns actually get paid to sleep, or is there more to it?
➡️ There’s more to it! Sleep interns track sleep, review products, and share insights—it’s not just about sleeping.
5. Do sleep interns really sleep all day, or do they have tasks to complete?
➡️ They have tasks! Interns journal their experiences, analyze sleep patterns, and test products to provide useful data.
6.Do you need to be an influencer to become a sleep intern?
➡️ No! While content creation helps, anyone passionate about sleep research and product testing can apply
